## Introduction

The Peer-to-Peer Rental Application enables users to rent products from other users within a peer-to-peer network. It facilitates the process of listing products, sending rental requests, managing listings, and handling payments. By leveraging Google OAuth, users can easily sign up or log in to the application.

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

Before getting started with the Peer-to-Peer Rental Application, ensure that you have the following prerequisites:

- Web browser with internet access
- Google account (for Google OAuth authentication)

### Installation

The Peer-to-Peer Rental Application is a web-based application and does not require any installation. Simply open your preferred web browser and navigate to the application's URL to access it.

## User Authentication

### Login/Signup with Google OAuth

To use the Peer-to-Peer Rental Application, you need to log in or sign up using your Google account. Follow these steps to authenticate with Google OAuth:

1. Visit the application's login/signup page.
2. Click on the "Login with Google" button.
3. You will be redirected to the Google login page.
4. Enter your Google account credentials.
5. Grant necessary permissions to the application when prompted.
6. You will be redirected back to the application and logged in successfully.

## Listing Products

### Creating a Listing

To list a product for renting, follow these steps:

1. Log in to the application using your Google account.
2. Navigate to your profile page.
3. Look for the "Create Listing" button and click on it.
4. Fill in the required details for the product, such as title, description, category, rental price, etc.
5. Upload relevant images of the product.
6. Click on the "Create" button to list the product.

### Updating a Listing

If you want to update the details of a product you have listed, follow these steps:

1. Log in to the application using your Google account.
2. Go to your profile page.
3. Find the listing you want to update.
4. Click on the "Edit" button or link associated with the listing.
5

. Modify the necessary details of the product.
6. Save the changes by clicking on the "Update" button.

### Deleting a Listing

If you wish to remove a product listing, follow these steps:

1. Log in to the application using your Google account.
2. Visit your profile page.
3. Locate the listing you want to delete.
4. Click on the "Delete" button or link associated with the listing.
5. Confirm the deletion when prompted.

## Rental Requests

### Sending a Rental Request

To send a rental request for a product, follow these steps:

1. Log in to the application using your Google account.
2. Browse through the available listings.
3. Select a product you want to rent.
4. Click on the "Rent Now" or "Send Rental Request" button.
5. Provide any necessary information or dates related to the rental.
6. Submit the rental request.

### Accepting/Rejecting a Rental Request

As a product owner, you can accept or reject rental requests sent by users. Follow these steps to manage rental requests:

1. Log in to the application using your Google account.
2. Access your profile page.
3. Look for the "Rental Requests" or "Manage Requests" section.
4. Review the pending rental requests.
5. Accept or reject requests based on your preferences.
6. Provide appropriate responses or instructions to the user.

## Payments

### Payment Due

When a rental request is accepted, users will receive a notification about the payment due. To make the payment, follow these steps:

1. Log in to the application using your Google account.
2. Access your profile page.
3. Look for the "Payment Due" section or notifications.
4. Click on the payment link or button.
5. Follow the provided instructions to complete the payment.

### Order Confirmation

After making the payment, users will receive an order confirmation. The order confirmation typically includes details about the rental period, pickup/delivery instructions, and any additional terms or agreements.

## Age Group

### Targeted Age Group

The Peer-to-Peer Rental Application is primarily targeted towards users between the ages of 18 and 30. The application is designed to cater to the preferences and needs of this specific age group.

